<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2244<hi rend="superscript">9/11</hi></note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Japanese Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Nomura</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-02">September 2, 1941</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Thank you for your letter
                            of August 29 in which you say that your Government “for various
                            considerations feels that secrecy at this time is essential for the
                            success of the conversations”; and that you therefore request my
                            cooperation in this regard.</p>
                        <p>I shall be glad to conform to the desires of yourself and your Government
                            in the foregoing respect, to every practical extent.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>[<signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi></signed>]</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>